# 📊 Exploratory Data Analysis on Retail Sales Data

## 📌 Project Overview

This project is part of the **Oasis Infobyte Data Analytics Internship (OIBSIP)**.

The objective is to perform **Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)** on a retail sales dataset to identify sales patterns, customer behavior, product performance, and generate actionable business insights using Python.

---

## 🎯 Objective

- Understand the structure of the retail sales dataset.
- Analyze sales trends over time.
- Study customer demographics.
- Identify top-performing products and categories.
- Discover relationships between numerical variables.
- Generate business recommendations based on the analysis.

---

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

- Python
- Pandas
- NumPy
- Matplotlib
- Seaborn
- Jupyter Notebook

---

## 📈 Analysis Performed

### ✅ Data Inspection

- Dataset shape
- Data types
- Missing value analysis
- Duplicate value check

---

### ✅ Descriptive Statistics

- Mean
- Median
- Mode
- Standard Deviation
- Summary statistics

---

### ✅ Time Series Analysis

- Monthly Sales Trend
- Quarterly Sales Trend
- Sales distribution over time

---

### ✅ Customer Demographics

- Customer age group distribution
- Gender distribution
- Purchase behavior analysis

---

### ✅ Product Analysis

- Top 10 Best-Selling Products
- Revenue by Product Category
- Product performance comparison

---

### ✅ Correlation Analysis

- Correlation Matrix
- Heatmap of numerical variables

---

### ✅ Additional Visualization

- Sales by Day of Week
- Revenue Distribution
- Customer Purchase Frequency

*(The visualization may vary depending on the dataset.)*

---

## 📊 Visualizations Used

- Line Charts
- Bar Charts
- Count Plots
- Histograms
- Box Plots
- Heatmap
- Pie Charts (where applicable)

---

## 🔍 Key Insights

- Identified peak sales periods through time series analysis.
- Determined the highest revenue-generating product categories.
- Analyzed customer demographics to understand purchasing behavior.
- Discovered correlations among sales-related numerical features.
- Revealed additional insights through custom visualizations.

---

## 💡 Business Recommendations

Based on the analysis:

1. Increase inventory for high-performing products during peak sales periods.
2. Focus marketing campaigns on the most profitable customer demographics.
3. Promote underperforming product categories using targeted discounts and offers.

---

## ▶️ How to Run

1. Clone the repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/Hil-Vasoya/OIBSIP.git
```

2. Navigate to the project folder

```bash
cd OIBSIP/DataAnalytics-L1-EDARetailSales
```

3. Install dependencies

```bash
pip install pandas numpy matplotlib seaborn jupyter
```

4. Launch Jupyter Notebook

```bash
jupyter notebook
```

5. Open

```
RetailSalesEDA.ipynb
```

---

## 📁 Dataset

The dataset contains retail sales information including:

- Sales Date
- Customer Information
- Product Details
- Quantity Sold
- Revenue
- Product Category

